ontrol. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223037","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223037r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","group_id":"V-223037","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1046-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59863","V-46997"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:565","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223037"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223038r961086","uuid":"F4E3CD8C-6C07-1014-B7EF-8CB129FF8EB8","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223038","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223038r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","group_id":"V-223038","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1051-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59871","V-47005"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:568","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223038"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverride\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223039r961194","uuid":"F4E3D102-6C07-1014-8C82-F202F725DAC5","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter prevents the user from browsing to or downloading from sites that are known to host malicious content. SmartScreen Filter also prevents the execution of files that are known to be malicious. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","group_id_src":"V-223039","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223039r961194_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","group_id":"V-223039","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1060-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79201","V-64711"],"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:578","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverride is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223039"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter.\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223040r961089","uuid":"F4E3D47E-6C07-1014-9453-ABD475CE09FD","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter warns the user about executable files that Internet Explorer users do not commonly download from the internet. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","group_id_src":"V-223040","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223040r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","group_id":"V-223040","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1065-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79203","V-64713"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ to âEnabledâ.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:572","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223040"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223041r961092","uuid":"F4E3D7F9-6C07-1014-B776-AC0F39FE2D61","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to prevent the installation of ActiveX controls on a per-user basis. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls cannot be installed on a per-user basis. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, ActiveX controls can be installed on a per-user basis.","group_id_src":"V-223041","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223041r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223041","rule_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1070-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79205","V-64715"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:574","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX\\BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223041"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventIgnoreCertErrors\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223042r961596","uuid":"F4E3DB5E-6C07-1014-BCBD-9161D2BECB56","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing (such as âexpiredâ, ârevokedâ, or âname mismatchâ errors) in Internet Explorer. If you enable this policy setting, the user cannot continue browsing. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose to ignore certificate errors and continue browsing.","group_id_src":"V-223042","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223042r961596_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","group_id":"V-223042","rule_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1075-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79207","V-64717"],"ccis":["CCI-001954"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:575","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\PreventIgnoreCertErrors is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000427","id":"V-223042"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223043r961194","uuid":"F4E3DEDE-6C07-1014-8582-D0E10EC928F5","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","group_id_src":"V-223043","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223043r961194_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","group_id":"V-223043","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1080-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79209","V-64719"],"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:577","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223043"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223044r961194","uuid":"F4E3E266-6C07-1014-B350-F74289F7DBE4","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","group_id_src":"V-223044","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223044r961194_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","group_id":"V-223044","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1085-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79211","V-64721"],"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:576","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223044"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223045r961092","uuid":"F4E3E5F1-6C07-1014-9BC0-CDD36CAB74E9","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","group_id_src":"V-223045","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223045r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223045","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1090-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79213","V-64723"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:579","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223045"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223046r961092","uuid":"F4E3E95E-6C07-1014-AE55-990162154749","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","group_id_src":"V-223046","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223046r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223046","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1095-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79215","V-64725"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:573","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223046"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" is set to âEnabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"RunThisTimeEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223048r960963","uuid":"F4E3EEA8-6C07-1014-AE9C-DC276CB9A6A9","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","group_id_src":"V-223048","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223048r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223048","rule_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1105-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-87395","V-72757"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" to \"Enabled\".","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:585","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\RunThisTimeEnabled is set to 0)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223048"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" is set to âDisabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"VersionCheckEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223049r960963","uuid":"F4E3F22D-6C07-1014-B2A2-84602783F428","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","group_id_src":"V-223049","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223049r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223049","rule_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1110-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-87397","V-72759"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:586","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\VersionCheckEnabled is set to 1)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223049"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223050r960963","uuid":"F4E3F5C9-6C07-1014-912B-A724690BD36F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users will not be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","group_id_src":"V-223050","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223050r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223050","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1115-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-87399","V-72761"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Pane &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:583","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223050"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223051r961089","uuid":"F4E3F95A-6C07-1014-8A31-DFAC83F82704","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone.","group_id_src":"V-223051","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223051r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","group_id":"V-223051","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI112-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59437","V-46573"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:436","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download signed ActiveX controls)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223051"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223052r960963","uuid":"F4E3FCE8-6C07-1014-A3EC-A401BAF8AD0B","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users wonât be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","group_id_src":"V-223052","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223052r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223052","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1120-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-87401","V-72763"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ.\n\nIn the Options windows, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.\n \n","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:584","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223052"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223053r961089","uuid":"F4E4009C-6C07-1014-8043-8D6C7EC0CDDF","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","group_id_src":"V-223053","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223053r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","group_id":"V-223053","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1125-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-89849","V-75169"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:588","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223053"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223054r961089","uuid":"F4E4046C-6C07-1014-86D7-8A16175BE04B","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. They must also be digitally signed.","group_id_src":"V-223054","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223054r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","group_id":"V-223054","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI113-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59439","V-46575"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:437","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download unsigned ActiveX controls)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223054"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223055r961089","uuid":"F4E408D5-6C07-1014-97C6-93A3ACF1F3AC","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","group_id_src":"V-223055","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223055r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","group_id":"V-223055","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1130-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-89851","V-75171"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:589","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone-&gt;'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223055"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ must be âEnabledâ. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKEY_LOCAL_Machine\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\nCriteria: If the value \"Disabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223056r961167","uuid":"F4E40CD0-6C07-1014-90A9-D8F1085C4AEC","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","group_id_src":"V-223056","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223056r961167_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","group_id":"V-223056","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","severity":"low","rule_version":"DTBI1135-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-106631","V-97527"],"ccis":["CCI-001312"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ to âEnabledâ.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:591","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Developer Tools are disabled)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000266","id":"V-223056"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223057r961092","uuid":"F4E41037-6C07-1014-95DF-ED3C8F4F0F4A","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"ActiveX controls not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","group_id_src":"V-223057","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223057r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223057","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI114-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59441","V-46577"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:438","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223057"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223058r961863","uuid":"F4E413CC-6C07-1014-9DCE-E13A511D2234","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether ActiveX controls and plug-ins can be run on pages from the specified zone. ActiveX controls not marked as safe should not be executed. If you enable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins can run without user intervention. If you disable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins are prevented from running.","group_id_src":"V-223058","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223058r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223058","rule_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI115-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59443","V-46579"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:439","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run ActiveX controls and plugins)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223058"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1405\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223059r961092","uuid":"F4E41754-6C07-1014-89C1-D13EE33E345F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows management of whether ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting can interact with a script. If you enable this policy setting, script interaction can occur automatically without user intervention. ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","group_id_src":"V-223059","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223059r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223059","rule_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI116-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59445","V-46581"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:440","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223059"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1803\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223060r960963","uuid":"F4E41AC3-6C07-1014-9B57-C85BD279EF46","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Sites located in the Restricted Sites Zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore downloads from this zone should be blocked. Files should not be able to be downloaded from sites that are considered restricted. This policy setting allows you to manage whether file downloads are permitted from the zone. This option is determined by the zone of the page with the link causing the download, not the zone from which the file is delivered.","group_id_src":"V-223060","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223060r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223060","rule_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI119-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59447","V-46583"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:441","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow file downloads)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223060"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223061r960963","uuid":"F4E41F0B-6C07-1014-8437-C4AAF64C380A","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223061","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223061r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223061","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI121-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59451","V-46587"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:453","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223061"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223062r1117169","uuid":"F4E426B4-6C07-1014-96DC-ACF6CD67259E","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","group_id_src":"V-223062","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223062r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","group_id":"V-223062","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI122-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59453","V-46589"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:443","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Access data sources across domains)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223062"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1608\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223063r961863","uuid":"F4E434B7-6C07-1014-8490-E1FF966A4547","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"It is possible that users will unknowingly be redirected to a site hosting malicious content. 'Allow META REFRESH' must have a level of protection based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether a user's browser can be redirected to another web page if the author of the web page uses the Meta Refresh setting to redirect browsers to another web page.","group_id_src":"V-223063","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223063r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223063","rule_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI123-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59455","V-46591"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:444","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow META REFRESH)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223063"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1802\" is REG_DWORD=3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223064r960963","uuid":"F4E43972-6C07-1014-A23E-836FAEA569C9","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Restricted Sites zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","group_id_src":"V-223064","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223064r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223064","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI126-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59457","V-46593"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:445","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223064"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223065r960963","uuid":"F4E43EC5-6C07-1014-8DC7-CA2333EDECAE","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","group_id_src":"V-223065","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223065r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223065","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI128-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59461","V-46597"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:447","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching applications and files in an IFRAME)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223065"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223066r1117169","uuid":"F4E44249-6C07-1014-92A1-CA69394C73AC","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Frames navigating across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","group_id_src":"V-223066","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223066r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","group_id":"V-223066","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI129-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59463","V-46599"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:448","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Navigate windows and frames across different domains)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223066"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223067r961128","uuid":"F4E445CB-6C07-1014-AE24-D54ED9C37800","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","group_id_src":"V-223067","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223067r961128_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","group_id":"V-223067","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI132-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59465","V-46601"],"ccis":["CCI-001199"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:449","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Userdata persistence)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-223067"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1400\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223068r960963","uuid":"F4E44959-6C07-1014-9C1A-D57DB2AD42ED","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Active scripts hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. Active scripting must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script code on pages in the zone are run.","group_id_src":"V-223068","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223068r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223068","rule_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI133-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59467","V-46603"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:450","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow active scripting)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223068"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223069r960963","uuid":"F4E44CC8-6C07-1014-94A6-E07E213E7ACA","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","group_id_src":"V-223069","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223069r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223069","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI134-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59469","V-46605"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:451","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow cut, copy, or paste operations from the clipboard via script)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223069"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Anonymous logon' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 196608 (decimal), this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223070r1043178","uuid":"F4E4508D-6C07-1014-97E4-CB8D0B9EA6B1","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. âAnonymous logonâ disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. âPrompt for user name and passwordâ queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon with current user name and passwordâ attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. The most secure option is to configure this setting to âEnabledâ; âAnonymous logonâ. This will prevent users from submitting credentials to servers in this security zone.","group_id_src":"V-223070","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223070r1043178_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","group_id":"V-223070","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI136-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59471","V-46607"],"ccis":["CCI-001184"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Anonymous logon' from the drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:452","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Logon options)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000219","id":"V-223070"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' must be 'Enabled', and '40' entered in 'Days to keep pages in History'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel Criteria: If the value \"History\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding. AND  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History Criteria: If the value \"DaysToKeep\" is REG_DWORD = 40 (decimal), this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223071r960879","uuid":"F4E45410-6C07-1014-AAF5-F71ABC9216AF","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This setting specifies the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The delete Browsing History option can be accessed using Tools, Internet Options, \"General\" tab, and then click Settings under Browsing History. If you enable this policy setting, a user cannot set the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List must be specified. Users will not be able to delete browsing history. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a user can set the number of days that Internet Explorer tracks views of pages in the History List. Users can delete browsing history.","group_id_src":"V-223071","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223071r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","group_id":"V-223071","rule_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI300-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59473","V-46609"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' to 'Enabled', and enter '40' in 'Days to keep pages in History'.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:513","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Disable Configuring History must be Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\40 entered in Days to keep pages in History)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223071"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_zones_map_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223072r960963","uuid":"F4E45777-6C07-1014-B114-AD908D84ECF9","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This setting prevents users from adding sites to various security zones. Users should not be able to add sites to different zones, as this could allow them to bypass security controls of the system. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will be able to add or remove sites from the Trusted Sites and Restricted Sites zones at will and change settings in the Local Intranet zone. This configuration could allow sites that host malicious mobile code to be added to these zones, and users could execute the code.","group_id_src":"V-223072","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223072r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223072","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI318-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59479","V-46615"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' to 'Enabled'.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:419","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Add/Delete Sites)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223072"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_options_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223073r961863","uuid":"F4E45ADA-6C07-1014-9FAF-92D723681FBB","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting prevents users from changing the Internet Explorer policies on the machine. Policy changes should be made by administrators only, so this setting should be enabled. If you enable this policy setting, you disable the \"Custom level\" button and \"Security\" level for this zone slider on the Security tab in the Internet Options dialog box. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users will be able to change the settings for security zones. It prevents users from changing security zone policy settings that are established by the administrator.","group_id_src":"V-223073","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223073r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223073","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI319-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59481","V-46617"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:418","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Change Policies)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223073"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_HKLM_only\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223074r961863","uuid":"F4E45E35-6C07-1014-942A-E487AD21AFCB","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting enforces consistent security zone settings to all users of the computer. Security zones control browser behavior at various websites and it is desirable to maintain a consistent policy for all users of a machine. This policy setting affects how security zone changes apply to different users. If you enable this policy setting, changes that one user makes to a security zone will apply to all users of that computer. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of the same computer are allowed to establish their own security zone settings.","group_id_src":"V-223074","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223074r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223074","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI320-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59483","V-46619"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' to 'Enabled'. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:417","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Use Only Machine Settings)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223074"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security Criteria: If the value \"DisableSecuritySettingsCheck\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223075r961863","uuid":"F4E461B7-6C07-1014-AC47-F84301F11422","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting turns off the Security Settings Check feature, which checks Internet Explorer security settings to determine when the settings put Internet Explorer at risk. If you enable this policy setting, the security settings check will not be performed. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the security settings check will be performed.","group_id_src":"V-223075","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223075r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223075","rule_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI325-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59485","V-46621"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' to 'Disabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:457","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn off the Security Settings Check feature)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223075"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Note: Some legitimate software and controls may have an invalid signature. You should carefully test such software in isolation before it is allowed to be used on an organization's network.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"RunInvalidSignatures\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223076r961092","uuid":"F4E46560-6C07-1014-9FF1-9E6A61D2075A","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls and file downloads often have digital signatures attached that certify the file's integrity and the identity of the signer (creator) of the software. Such signatures help ensure unmodified software is downloaded and the user can positively identify the signer to determine whether you trust them enough to run their software.","group_id_src":"V-223076","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223076r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223076","rule_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI350-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59489","V-46625"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' to 'Disabled'. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:459","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Allow Software to Run or Install Even if the Signature is Invalid)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223076"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Isolation64Bit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223077r961131","uuid":"F4E468F0-6C07-1014-BADE-8924B9ACF749","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer 11 uses 64-bit processes (for greater security) or 32-bit processes (for greater compatibility) when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows.Important: Some ActiveX controls and toolbars may not be available when 64-bit processes are used. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 32-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you don't configure this policy setting, users can turn this feature on or off using Internet Explorer settings. This feature is turned off by default.","group_id_src":"V-223077","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223077r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","group_id":"V-223077","rule_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI356-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59861","V-46995"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:564","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223077"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"CertificateRevocation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223078r961038","uuid":"F4E46C6E-6C07-1014-8A87-C0D6AB093E80","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer will check revocation status of servers' certificates. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check to see if server certificates have been revoked. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","group_id_src":"V-223078","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223078r961038_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","group_id":"V-223078","rule_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","severity":"low","rule_version":"DTBI365-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59493","V-46629"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:461","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Server Certificate Revocation)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-223078"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"CheckExeSignatures\" is REG_SZ = yes, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223079r960954","uuid":"F4E47012-6C07-1014-B3AC-A90AC3D6347B","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer checks for digital signatures (which identifies the publisher of signed software and verifies it has not been modified or tampered with) on user computers before downloading executable programs. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check the digital signatures of executable programs and display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you do not configure this policy, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers.","group_id_src":"V-223079","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223079r960954_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","group_id":"V-223079","rule_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI370-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59497","V-46633"],"ccis":["CCI-001749"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:462","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Signature on Downloaded Programs)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000131","id":"V-223079"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap Criteria: If the value \"UNCAsIntranet\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223080r961863","uuid":"F4E47398-6C07-1014-838A-97EA9D196279","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Some UNC paths could refer to servers not managed by the organization, which means they could host malicious content; and therefore, it is safest to not include all UNC paths in the Intranet Sites zone. This policy setting controls whether URLs representing UNCs are mapped into the local Intranet security zone. If you enable this policy setting, all network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone. If you disable this policy setting, network paths are not necessarily mapped into the Intranet Zone (other rules might map one there). If you do not configure this policy setting, users choose whether network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone.","group_id_src":"V-223080","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223080r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223080","rule_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI375-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59499","V-46635"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' to 'Disabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:463","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs))\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223080"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223081r960963","uuid":"F4E47744-6C07-1014-B6FC-F8649BD7B3EE","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","group_id_src":"V-223081","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223081r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223081","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI385-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59501","V-46637"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:464","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223081"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223082r960963","uuid":"F4E47B00-6C07-1014-A4B5-DE6619995AE2","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","group_id_src":"V-223082","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223082r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223082","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI390-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59503","V-46639"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:465","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223082"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223083r960963","uuid":"F4E47EBE-6C07-1014-AFCB-8516C6A10ED7","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","group_id_src":"V-223083","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223083r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223083","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI395-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59505","V-46641"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:466","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223083"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223084r960963","uuid":"F4E4825D-6C07-1014-8C7C-9CCBFB849EAF","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","group_id_src":"V-223084","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223084r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223084","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI415-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59507","V-46643"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:467","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223084"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223085r960963","uuid":"F4E48625-6C07-1014-8C7F-A959AA24232D","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.  ","group_id_src":"V-223085","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223085r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223085","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI425-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59509","V-46645"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:468","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223085"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt;Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223086r961086","uuid":"F4E48B0E-6C07-1014-9A63-AF9DA2E08D2E","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223086","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223086r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","group_id":"V-223086","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI426-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59869","V-47003"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:567","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223086"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223087r960963","uuid":"F4E48EDA-6C07-1014-965F-B81BD10CD55D","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223087","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223087r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223087","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI430-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59511","V-46647"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:469","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223087"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value\" 1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223088r960963","uuid":"F4E49286-6C07-1014-8320-E322E5D4F907","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223088","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223088r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223088","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI435-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59513","V-46649"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:470","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Intranet Zone\\Java permissions)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223088"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223089r960963","uuid":"F4E49614-6C07-1014-A5AC-D308B9ACE8F8","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","group_id_src":"V-223089","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223089r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223089","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI440-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59517","V-46653"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:471","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Trusted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223089"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223090r960963","uuid":"F4E499BE-6C07-1014-A2CF-DB77BC03959F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","group_id_src":"V-223090","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223090r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223090","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI450-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59527","V-46663"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:473","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223090"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223091r961863","uuid":"F4E49D3F-6C07-1014-9F83-DAF4D3979606","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","group_id_src":"V-223091","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223091r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223091","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI455-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59529","V-46665"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:474","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Loose or un-compiled XAML files)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223091"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223092r961863","uuid":"F4E4A0A8-6C07-1014-A5BE-87D8FBE29608","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","group_id_src":"V-223092","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223092r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223092","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI460-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59533","V-46669"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:475","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Loose XAML files)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223092"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223093r961131","uuid":"F4E4A453-6C07-1014-93FE-EB0AAFC851CD","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","group_id_src":"V-223093","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223093r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","group_id":"V-223093","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI485-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59545","V-46681"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:480","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223093"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223094r961131","uuid":"F4E4A7C8-6C07-1014-A497-D299BD10A993","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","group_id_src":"V-223094","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223094r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","group_id":"V-223094","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI490-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59549","V-46685"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled' and select 'Enable', from the drop-down box.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:481","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223094"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223095r960963","uuid":"F4E4AB3B-6C07-1014-862C-A3ED2F95A7AF","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","group_id_src":"V-223095","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223095r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223095","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI495-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59553","V-46689"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:482","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223095"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223096r960963","uuid":"F4E4AEAC-6C07-1014-B6FD-8A8418B487BF","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","group_id_src":"V-223096","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223096r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223096","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI500-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59555","V-46691"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:483","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223096"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223097r1117169","uuid":"F4E4B276-6C07-1014-B4CB-C927343F89C2","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows a user to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Internet zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If \"Prompt\" is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","group_id_src":"V-223097","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223097r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","group_id":"V-223097","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI515-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59557","V-46693"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:484","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223097"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223098r1117169","uuid":"F4E4B61C-6C07-1014-97CD-9393F2A53090","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Restricted zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If Prompt is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","group_id_src":"V-223098","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223098r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","group_id":"V-223098","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI520-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59559","V-46695"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:485","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223098"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2000\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223099r960963","uuid":"F4E4B9AD-6C07-1014-B1F7-B4A01FD7DA49","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage dynamic binary and script behaviors of components that encapsulate specific functionality for HTML elements, to which they were attached. If you enable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.   If you select \"Administrator approved\" in the drop-down box, only the behaviors listed in the Admin-approved Behaviors under Binary Behaviors Security Restriction policy are available.    If you disable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are not available unless applications have implemented a custom security manager. If you do not configure this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.","group_id_src":"V-223099","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223099r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223099","rule_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI575-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59565","V-46701"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:486","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow binary and script behaviors)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223099"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223100r960963","uuid":"F4E4C45C-6C07-1014-909E-F533E26203E7","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","group_id_src":"V-223100","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223100r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223100","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI580-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59569","V-46705"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:487","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223100"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223101r961083","uuid":"F4E4C8DE-6C07-1014-8925-9ECD1F0F93C5","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting your network.","group_id_src":"V-223101","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223101r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id":"V-223101","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI590-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59573","V-46709"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:488","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223101"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223102r961083","uuid":"F4E4CCF1-6C07-1014-8E49-905AAB2168BA","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to the organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","group_id_src":"V-223102","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223102r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id":"V-223102","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI592-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59575","V-46711"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:502","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223102"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223103r961083","uuid":"F4E4D0D8-6C07-1014-AE25-BDDFFF73F433","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates that the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure that executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","group_id_src":"V-223103","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223103r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id":"V-223103","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI594-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59577","V-46713"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:503","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223103"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223104r961083","uuid":"F4E4D46A-6C07-1014-8E6A-CD36FD60E523","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends you configure this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","group_id_src":"V-223104","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223104r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id":"V-223104","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI595-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59579","V-46715"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:489","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223104"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223105r961083","uuid":"F4E4D904-6C07-1014-84FF-9AF41D80ADBB","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","group_id_src":"V-223105","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223105r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id":"V-223105","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI596-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59581","V-46717"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:510","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223105"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223106r961083","uuid":"F4E4DCCC-6C07-1014-9643-D1E3A270DD10","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","group_id_src":"V-223106","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223106r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id":"V-223106","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI597-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59583","V-46719"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:511","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223106"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223107r960963","uuid":"F4E4E094-6C07-1014-91E3-DAA1658E2403","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","group_id_src":"V-223107","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223107r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223107","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI599-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59585","V-46721"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:504","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223107"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223108r960963","uuid":"F4E4E40B-6C07-1014-A569-C173C236EFEC","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","group_id_src":"V-223108","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223108r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223108","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI600-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59587","V-46723"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:490","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223108"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223109r960963","uuid":"F4E4E7E8-6C07-1014-9990-917FB45FAB50","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","group_id_src":"V-223109","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223109r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223109","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI605-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59589","V-46725"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:491","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223109"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223110r961131","uuid":"F4E4EB70-6C07-1014-AB21-BA305422E57A","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","group_id_src":"V-223110","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223110r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","group_id":"V-223110","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI610-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59591","V-46727"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:492","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223110"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223111r961131","uuid":"F4E4EEE3-6C07-1014-BDCF-83F3C8847D86","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends configuring this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","group_id_src":"V-223111","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223111r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","group_id":"V-223111","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI612-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59593","V-46729"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:505","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223111"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223112r961131","uuid":"F4E4F238-6C07-1014-BB55-C9CECFAB0A1E","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","group_id_src":"V-223112","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223112r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","group_id":"V-223112","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI614-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59595","V-46731"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:506","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223112"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223113r960963","uuid":"F4E4F586-6C07-1014-BEFD-B6D37BE3CBAF","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","group_id_src":"V-223113","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223113r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223113","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI630-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59597","V-46733"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:493","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\ Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223113"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223114r960963","uuid":"F4E4F903-6C07-1014-A88D-B0EBCCC7E628","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","group_id_src":"V-223114","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223114r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223114","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI635-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59645","V-46779"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:494","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223114"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223115r960963","uuid":"F4E4FC6C-6C07-1014-92B9-B1D6F84B13A5","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","group_id_src":"V-223115","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223115r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223115","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI640-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59647","V-46781"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:495","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223115"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223116r960963","uuid":"F4E50019-6C07-1014-924E-973F5793F959","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force the user to interact with a window containing malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and create windows that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","group_id_src":"V-223116","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223116r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223116","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI645-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59653","V-46787"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:496","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223116"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223117r960963","uuid":"F4E503A4-6C07-1014-8132-DBCD8AF521BA","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","group_id_src":"V-223117","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223117r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223117","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI647-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59655","V-46789"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:507","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223117"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223118r960963","uuid":"F4E50715-6C07-1014-B3CB-FD95796BFE45","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","group_id_src":"V-223118","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223118r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223118","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI649-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59657","V-46791"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:508","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223118"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223119r961863","uuid":"F4E50AA2-6C07-1014-85A6-CCCDC90A34FC","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223119","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223119r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223119","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI650-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59663","V-46797"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:497","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223119"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223120r961863","uuid":"F4E50E36-6C07-1014-9CCF-E9FA600C25BB","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. It may be possible for malicious content hosted on a website to take advantage of these components. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223120","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223120r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223120","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI655-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59665","V-46799"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:498","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223120"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223121r960963","uuid":"F4E511AC-6C07-1014-9410-D46E93187F11","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applets are exposed to scripts within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow scripts to access applets. If you disable this policy setting, scripts are prevented from accessing applets. If you do not configure this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. ","group_id_src":"V-223121","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223121r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223121","rule_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI670-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59667","V-46801"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:499","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Scripting of Java applets)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223121"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Use FormSuggest\" is REG_SZ = no, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223122r960963","uuid":"F4E51521-6C07-1014-8F49-B8922431D24E","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This AutoComplete feature suggests possible matches when users are filling in forms. It is possible that this feature will cache sensitive data and store it in the user's profile, where it might not be protected as rigorously as required by organizational policy. If you enable this setting, the user is not presented with suggested matches when filling in forms. If you disable this setting, the user is presented with suggested possible matches when filling forms. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom to turn on the auto-complete feature for forms. To display this option, the user opens the Internet Options dialog box, clicks the \"Contents\" tab, and clicks the \"Settings\" button.","group_id_src":"V-223122","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223122r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223122","rule_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI690-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59673","V-46807"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223122","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223122"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions Criteria: If the value \"NoCrashDetection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223123r960963","uuid":"F4E51884-6C07-1014-B51B-BB4D87538E6F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"The 'Turn off Crash Detection' policy setting allows you to manage the crash detection feature of add-on management in Internet Explorer. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you enable this policy setting, a crash in Internet Explorer will be similar to one on a computer running Windows XP Professional Service Pack 1 and earlier, where Windows Error Reporting will be invoked. If you disable this policy setting, the crash detection feature in add-on management will be functional. ","group_id_src":"V-223123","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223123r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223123","rule_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI715-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59677","V-46811"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:509","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn Off Crash Detection)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223123"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' must be 'Disabled'. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest Passwords\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding. AND Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest PW Ask\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223124r960963","uuid":"F4E51BE9-6C07-1014-8DE1-D726FF5913D4","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls automatic completion of fields in forms on web pages. It is possible that malware could be developed which would be able to extract the cached user names and passwords from the currently logged on user, which an attacker could then use to compromise that user's online accounts.  If you enable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for\" User names and passwords on forms\" will be turned on. If you disable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for \"User names and passwords on forms\" is turned off. The user also cannot opt to be prompted to save passwords. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom of turning on Auto Complete for \"User name and passwords on forms\", and the option of prompting to save passwords.","group_id_src":"V-223124","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223124r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223124","rule_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI725-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59681","V-46815"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' to 'Disabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223124","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223124"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"On\" selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnabledV9\" is \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223125r961083","uuid":"F4E51F7E-6C07-1014-B2CE-F94412C44906","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This setting is important from a security perspective because Microsoft has extensive data illustrating the positive impact the SmartScreen filter has had on reducing the risk of malware infection via visiting malicious websites. This policy setting allows users to enable the SmartScreen Filter, which will warn if the website being visited is known for fraudulent attempts to gather personal information through 'phishing' or is known to host malware. If you enable this setting the user will not be prompted to enable the SmartScreen Filter. It must be specified which mode the SmartScreen Filter uses: On or Off. If the feature is On, all website addresses not contained on the filters allow list, will be sent automatically to Microsoft without prompting the user. If this feature is set to Off, the feature will not run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user is prompted to decide whether to turn on SmartScreen Filter during the first-run experience.","group_id_src":"V-223125","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223125r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id":"V-223125","rule_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI740-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59685","V-46819"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"On\" from the drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:514","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223125"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223126r960879","uuid":"F4E522DF-6C07-1014-8C78-CC97BA62097D","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Delete Browsing History on exit automatically deletes specified items when the last browser window closes.  Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures.  Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","group_id_src":"V-223126","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223126r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","group_id":"V-223126","rule_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI760-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59695","V-46829"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' to 'Disabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:516","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Configure Delete Browsing History on exit)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223126"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"CleanHistory\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223127r960879","uuid":"F4E5278C-6C07-1014-A398-C4961201A3AD","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy prevents users from deleting the history of websites the user has visited. If you enable this policy setting, websites the user has visited will be preserved when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you disable this policy setting, websites that the user has visited will be deleted when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you do not configure this policy setting, the user will be able to select whether to delete or preserve websites the user visited when the user clicks \"Delete\".","group_id_src":"V-223127","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223127r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","group_id":"V-223127","rule_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI770-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59707","V-46841"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:517","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223127"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"EnableInPrivateBrowsing\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223128r960864","uuid":"F4E52B1E-6C07-1014-B98F-ECEAE36F5639","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"InPrivate Browsing lets the user control whether or not Internet Explorer saves the browsing history, cookies, and other data. User control of settings is not the preferred control method. The InPrivate Browsing feature in Internet Explorer makes browser privacy easy by not storing history, cookies, temporary Internet files, or other data. If you enable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be disabled. If you disable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be available for use. If you do not configure this setting, InPrivate Browsing can be turned on or off through the registry.","group_id_src":"V-223128","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223128r960864_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","group_id":"V-223128","rule_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI780-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59713","V-46847"],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:518","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\InPrivate\\Turn off InPrivate Browsing)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-223128"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223129r960963","uuid":"F4E52E7A-6C07-1014-8E99-A450DD9FB79E","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","group_id_src":"V-223129","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223129r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223129","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI800-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59715","V-46849"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:519","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223129"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223130r960963","uuid":"F4E53230-6C07-1014-8FDB-FB7009735867","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","group_id_src":"V-223130","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223130r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223130","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI810-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59719","V-46853"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:520","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223130"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223131r960963","uuid":"F4E535E7-6C07-1014-BB62-CF36CED22927","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223131","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223131r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223131","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI815-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59723","V-46857"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:541","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223131"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223132r961863","uuid":"F4E53B4E-6C07-1014-9999-86AE49DEB72F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \" Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","group_id_src":"V-223132","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223132r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223132","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI820-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59725","V-46859"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:521","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223132"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223133r960963","uuid":"F4E53EE0-6C07-1014-907E-8FFB67293284","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223133","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223133r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223133","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI825-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59727","V-46861"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:542","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223133"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; ' Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223134r961092","uuid":"F4E5428D-6C07-1014-9B5E-ED750F4C300E","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","group_id_src":"V-223134","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223134r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223134","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI830-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59729","V-46865"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:522","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223134"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223135r960963","uuid":"F4E545FF-6C07-1014-BF85-C8323E01FB45","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223135","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223135r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223135","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI835-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59735","V-46869"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:543","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223135"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223136r960963","uuid":"F4E54984-6C07-1014-8A6D-8F69AB9D2382","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","group_id_src":"V-223136","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223136r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223136","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI840-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59745","V-46879"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:523","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter must be Enabled and Enable selected)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223136"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223137r960963","uuid":"F4E54CF6-6C07-1014-B28A-8B7FF543065F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser Control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser Control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","group_id_src":"V-223137","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223137r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223137","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI850-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59749","V-46883"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:524","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223137"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223138r960963","uuid":"F4E55064-6C07-1014-92E8-98157CCAF046","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","group_id_src":"V-223138","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223138r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223138","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI860-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59751","V-46885"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:525","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223138"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223139r961863","uuid":"F4E553CF-6C07-1014-8E1A-DFDC5103C90F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \"Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","group_id_src":"V-223139","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223139r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223139","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI870-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59755","V-46889"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:526","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223139"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223140r961092","uuid":"F4E5573D-6C07-1014-9452-8623B5530233","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","group_id_src":"V-223140","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223140r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id":"V-223140","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI880-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59759","V-46893"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:527","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223140"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223141r960963","uuid":"F4E55AB3-6C07-1014-B430-FDF509B3A511","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","group_id_src":"V-223141","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223141r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223141","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI890-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59761","V-46895"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:528","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223141"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223142r960921","uuid":"F4E55E5D-6C07-1014-AF33-80A8A92AFF8D","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223142","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223142r960921_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","group_id":"V-223142","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI900-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59763","V-46897"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:529","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-223142"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223143r960963","uuid":"F4E561C4-6C07-1014-97C6-B7399C4DF1D2","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause them to perform an undesirable action. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","group_id_src":"V-223143","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223143r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223143","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI910-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59769","V-46903"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:530","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disable selected)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223143"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223144r961863","uuid":"F4E56573-6C07-1014-94E7-BAD18BE3E75D","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Unsigned components are more likely to contain malicious code and it is more difficult to determine the author of the application - therefore they should be avoided if possible. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223144","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223144r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223144","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI920-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59773","V-46907"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:531","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223144"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223145r961863","uuid":"F4E568E7-6C07-1014-ADEA-A93E90A39FB7","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"It may be possible for someone to host malicious content on a website that takes advantage of these components. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223145","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223145r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223145","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI930-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59787","V-46921"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:532","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223145"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223146r960963","uuid":"F4E56C4B-6C07-1014-92DC-E175FE6B386C","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","group_id_src":"V-223146","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223146r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223146","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI940-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59793","V-46927"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:533","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223146"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223147r960963","uuid":"F4E56FAE-6C07-1014-B083-D4CE620F33D2","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause an undesirable action. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","group_id_src":"V-223147","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223147r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id":"V-223147","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI950-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59805","V-46939"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:534","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disabled selected)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223147"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"DisableEPMCompat\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-223148r961863","uuid":"F4E5743A-6C07-1014-9CCC-948464E9D299","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This setting prevents ActiveX controls from running in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled. When a user has an ActiveX control installed that is not compatible with Enhanced Protected Mode and a website attempts to load the control, Internet Explorer notifies the user and gives the option to run the website in regular Protected Mode. This policy setting disables this notification and forces all websites to run in Enhanced Protected Mode. Enhanced Protected Mode provides additional protection against malicious websites by using 64-bit processes on 64-bit versions of Windows. For computers running at least Windows 8, Enhanced Protected Mode also limits the locations Internet Explorer can read from in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not give the user the option to disable Enhanced Protected Mode. All Protected Mode websites will run in Enhanced Protected Mode. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer notifies users and provides an option to run websites with incompatible ActiveX controls in regular Protected Mode.","group_id_src":"V-223148","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223148r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id":"V-223148","rule_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI985-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59841","V-46975"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' to 'Enabled'.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:556","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Advanced Page/Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode )\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223148"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223149r1117169","uuid":"F4E577FD-6C07-1014-8823-F396EE5FF70A","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","group_id_src":"V-223149","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-223149r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","group_id":"V-223149","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI990-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59847","V-46981"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:547","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223149"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" must be \"Enabled\".\n\nVerify the only option selected is \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings!SecureProtocols.\n\nCriteria: If the value for \"SecureProtocols\" is not REG_DWORD = \"2048\", this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-250540r1117186","uuid":"F4E57B79-6C07-1014-B5B6-E973AE8AB555","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DOD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by allowing the user to turn on/off support for TLS and SSL. TLS is a protocol for protecting communications between the browser and the target server. When the browser attempts to set up a protected communication with the target server, the browser and server negotiate which protocol and version to use. The browser and server attempt to match each other's list of supported protocols and versions and pick the most preferred match.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","group_id_src":"V-250540","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-250540r1117186_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","group_id":"V-250540","rule_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI014-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59337","V-46473"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSelect only \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:580","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('turn off encryption support' setting is handled by Group Policy.)\nTest            :   true (TLS 1.2 must be selected for the IE option 'turn off encryption support' via Group Policy.)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000416","id":"V-250540"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"No Sites\" selected from the drop-down box. If \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" is not \"Enabled\" or any other drop-down option is selected, this is a finding. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableSSL3Fallback\" is REG_DWORD=0, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-250541r1117186","uuid":"F4E57ECA-6C07-1014-9DA3-C9B960E32346","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DoD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by blocking an insecure fallback to SSL when TLS 1.0 or greater fails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","group_id_src":"V-250541","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-250541r1117186_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","group_id":"V-250541","rule_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI1100-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79219","V-64729"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"No Sites\" from the drop-down box.\n","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:581","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Allow insecure fallback for:' set to 'No Sites')\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000416","id":"V-250541"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Internet Explorer 11 is no longer supported by the vendor.\n\nIf Internet Explorer 11 is installed, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-252910r1156566","uuid":"F4E589BA-6C07-1014-959F-9708B85CFC34","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may depend on the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.","group_id_src":"V-252910","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-252910r1156566_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","group_id":"V-252910","rule_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","severity":"high","rule_version":"DTBI999-IE11","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"fix_text":"Remove the Internet Explorer 11 application.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.win:def:252910","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:55:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Internet Explorer 11 is installed)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"open","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-252910"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"4095","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F4D2DE84-6C07-1014-96C0-B81BD2946E3A","comments":null}],"reference_identifier":"4095","size":137,"stig_id":"IE_11_STIG","release_info":"Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","stig_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11 Security Technical Implementation Guide"},{"display_name":"Microsoft SQL Server 2022 Instance","version":"1","uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","rules":[{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Review the system documentation to determine whether any concurrent session limits have been defined. If it does not, assume a limit of 10 for database administrators and two for all other users. \n \nIf a mechanism other than a logon trigger is used, verify its correct operation by the appropriate means. If it does not work correctly, this is a finding.\n\nDue to excessive CPU consumption when using a logon trigger, an alternative method of limiting concurrent sessions is setting the max connection limit within SQL Server to an appropriate value. This serves to block a distributed denial-of-service (DDOS) attack by limiting the attacker's connections while allowing a database administrator to still force a SQL connection.\n\nIn SQL Server Management Studio's Object Explorer tree, right-click on the Server Name &gt;&gt; Properties &gt;&gt; Connections Tab.\n\nOR\n\nRun the query:\nEXEC sys.sp_configure N'user connections'\n\nIf the max connection limit is set to 0 (unlimited) or does not match the documented value, this is a finding.\n \nOtherwise, determine if a logon trigger exists:  \n \nIn SQL Server Management Studio's Object Explorer tree, expand [SQL Server Instance] &gt;&gt; Server Objects &gt;&gt; Triggers.\n \nOR \n \nRun the query:  \nSELECT name FROM master.sys.server_triggers;  \n \nIf no triggers are listed, this is a finding. \n \nIf triggers are listed, identify the trigger(s) limiting the number of concurrent sessions per user. If none are found, this is a finding. If they are present but disabled, this is a finding. \n \nExamine the trigger source code for logical correctness and for compliance with the documented limit(s). If errors or variances exist, this is a finding.\n \nVerify that the system does execute the trigger(s) each time a user session is established. If it does not operate correctly for all types of user, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271263r1108405","uuid":"43C7EC84-6C08-1014-8512-B05E732918BD","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Database management includes the ability to control the number of users and user sessions using a DBMS. Unlimited concurrent connections to the DBMS could allow a successful denial-of-service (DoS) attack by exhausting connection resources; and a system can also fail or be degraded by an overload of legitimate users. Limiting the number of concurrent sessions per user is helpful in reducing these risks.\n\nThis requirement addresses concurrent session control for a single account. It does not address concurrent sessions by a single user via multiple system accounts; and it does not deal with the total number of sessions across all accounts.\n\nThe capability to limit the number of concurrent sessions per user must be configured in or added to the DBMS (for example, by use of a logon trigger), when this is technically feasible. Note that it is not sufficient to limit sessions via a web server or application server alone, because legitimate users and adversaries can potentially connect to the DBMS by other means.\n\nThe organization will need to define the maximum number of concurrent sessions by account type, by account, or a combination thereof. In deciding on the appropriate number, it is important to consider the work requirements of the various types of users. For example, two might be an acceptable limit for general users accessing the database via an application; but 10 might be too few for a database administrator using a database management GUI tool, where each query tab and navigation pane may count as a separate session.\n\nSessions may also be referred to as connections or logons, which for the purposes of this requirement are synonyms.","group_id_src":"V-271263","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271263r1108405_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000001-DB-000031","group_id":"V-271263","rule_title":"SQL Server must limit the number of concurrent sessions to an organization-defined number per user for all accounts and/or account types.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-003600","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000054"],"fix_text":"If a trigger consumes too much CPU, an example alternative method for limiting the concurrent users is setting the max connection limit on SQL Server.\n\nIn SQL Server Management Studio's Object Explorer tree, right-click on the Server Name &gt;&gt; Properties &gt;&gt; Connections Tab &gt;&gt; Set the Maximum Number of Concurrent Connections to a value other than 0 (0 = unlimited), and document it.\n\nOR\n\nRun the query:\n\nEXEC sys.sp_configure N'user connections','5000' /* this is an example max limit */\nGO\nRECONFIGURE WITH OVERRIDE\nGO\n\nRestart SQL Server for the setting to take effect.\n\nReference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/database-engine/configure-windows/configure-the-user-connections-server-configuration-option?\n\nOtherwise, establish the limit(s) appropriate to the type(s) of user account accessing the SQL Server instance, and record them in the system documentation. Implement one or more logon triggers to enforce the limit(s), without exposing the dynamic management views to general users. \n\nExample script:\n \nCREATE TRIGGER SQL_STIG_Connection_Limit \nON ALL SERVER WITH EXECUTE AS 'renamed_sa' /*Make sure to use the renamed SA account here*/ \nFOR LOGON \nAS \nBEGIN \nIf (Select COUNT(1) from sys.dm_exec_sessions WHERE is_user_process = 1 AND original_login_name = ORIGINAL_LOGIN() ) &gt; \n  (CASE ORIGINAL_LOGIN()\n              WHEN 'domain/ima.dba' THEN 150    /*this is a busy DBA's domain account */\n              WHEN 'application1_login' THEN 6  /* this is a SQL login for an application */\n              WHEN 'application2_login' THEN 20 /* this is a SQL login for another application */\n              â¦\n              ELSE 1 /* All unspecified users are restricted to a single login */\n  END)\n              BEGIN \n                             PRINT 'The login [' + ORIGINAL_LOGIN() + '] has exceeded its concurrent session limit.' \n                             ROLLBACK; \n              END\nEND; \n  \nReference: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms189799.aspx","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:101","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-271263, SV-271263r1108405, SRG-APP-000001-DB-000031)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000001-DB-000031","id":"V-271263"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"If the SQL Server is not part of an Active Directory domain, this is Not Applicable. \n\nObtain the fully qualified domain name of the SQL Server instance: \n\n1. Launch Windows Explorer. \n2. Right-click \"Computer\" or \"This PC\" (Varies by OS level). \n3. Click \"Properties\". Note the value shown for \"Full computer name\". \n\nNote: For a cluster, this value must be obtained from the Failover Cluster Manager.\n\nObtain the TCP port that is supporting the SQL Server instance:\n \n1. Click \"Start\".\n2. Type \"SQL Server 2022 Configuration Manager\".\n3. From the search results, click \"SQL Server 2022 Configuration Manager\". \n4. From the tree on the left, expand \"SQL Server Network Configuration\". \n5. Click \"Protocols for &lt;Instance Name&gt;\" where &lt;Instance Name&gt; is the name of the instance (MSSQLSERVER is the default name). \n6. In the right pane, right-click \"TCP/IP\" and choose \"Properties\". \n7. In the window that opens, click the \"IP Addresses\" tab. Note the TCP port configured for the instance. \n\nObtain the service account that is running the SQL Server service: \n\n1. Click \"Start\". \n2. Type \"SQL Server 2022 Configuration Manager\". \n3. From the search results, click \"SQL Server 2022 Configuration Manager\". \n4. From the tree on the left, select \"SQL Server Services\". Note the account listed in the \"Log On As\" column for the SQL Server instance being reviewed. \n5. Launch a command-line or PowerShell window. \n6. Enter the following command where &lt;Service Account&gt; is the identity of the service account:\n      setspn -L &lt;Service Account&gt; \n      Example: setspn -L CONTOSO\\sql2016svc \n7. Review the Registered Service Principal Names returned. \n\nIf the listing does not contain the following supported service principal names (SPN) formats, this is a finding. \n\nNamed instance\n   MSSQLSvc/&lt;FQDN&gt;:[&lt;port&gt; | &lt;instancename&gt;], where:\n   MSSQLSvc is the service that is being registered.\n   &lt;FQDN&gt; is the fully qualified domain name of the server.\n   &lt;port&gt; is the TCP port number.\n   &lt;instancename&gt; is the name of the SQL Server instance.\n\nDefault instance\n   MSSQLSvc/&lt;FQDN&gt;:&lt;port&gt; | MSSQLSvc/&lt;FQDN&gt;, where:\n   MSSQLSvc is the service that is being registered.\n   &lt;FQDN&gt; is the fully qualified domain name of the server.\n   &lt;port&gt; is the TCP port number.\n\nIf the MSSQLSvc service is registered for any fully qualified domain names that do not match the current server, this may indicate the service account is shared across SQL Server instances. Review server documentation, if the sharing of service accounts across instances is not documented and authorized, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271264r1111061","uuid":"43C7F33B-6C08-1014-842A-9C34C97230DC","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Enterprise environments make account management for applications and databases challenging and complex. A manual process for account management functions adds the risk of a potential oversight or other error. Managing accounts for the same person in multiple places is inefficient and prone to problems with consistency and synchronization. \n \nA comprehensive application account management process that includes automation helps to ensure that accounts designated as requiring attention are consistently and promptly addressed. \n \nExamples include, but are not limited to, using automation to act on multiple accounts designated as inactive, suspended, or terminated, or by disabling accounts located in noncentralized account stores, such as multiple servers. Account management functions can also include assignment of group or role membership; identifying account type; specifying user access authorizations (i.e., privileges); account removal, update, or termination; and administrative alerts. The use of automated mechanisms can include, for example: using email or text messaging to notify account managers when users are terminated or transferred; using the information system to monitor account usage; and using automated telephone notification to report atypical system account usage. \n \nSQL Server must be configured to automatically use organization-level account management functions, and these functions must immediately enforce the organization's current account policy. \n \nAutomation may comprise differing technologies that when placed together contain an overall mechanism supporting an organization's automated account management requirements. \n \nSQL Server supports several authentication methods to allow operation in various environments, Kerberos, NTLM, and SQL Server. An instance of SQL Server must be configured to use the most secure method available. Service accounts used by SQL Server should be unique to a given instance.","group_id_src":"V-271264","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271264r1111061_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000023-DB-000001","group_id":"V-271264","rule_title":"SQL Server must be configured to use the most-secure authentication method available.","severity":"high","rule_version":"SQLI-22-003800","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000015"],"fix_text":"Ensure Service Principal Names (SPNs) are properly registered for the SQL Server instance. \n\nUse the Microsoft Kerberos Configuration Manager to review Kerberos configuration issues for a given SQL Server instance. \n\nhttps://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=39046 \n\nAlternatively, SPNs for SQL Server can be manually registered. \n\nFor other connections that support Kerberos the SPN is registered in the format MSSQLSvc/&lt;FQDN&gt;/&lt;instancename&gt; for a named instance. The format for registering the default instance is MSSQLSvc/&lt;FQDN&gt;.\n\nUsing an account with permissions to register SPNs, issue the following commands from a command-prompt: \n\nsetspn -S MSSQLSvc/&lt;Fully Qualified Domain Name&gt; &lt;Service Account&gt; \nsetspn -S MSSQLSvc/&lt;Fully Qualified Domain Name&gt;:&lt;TCP Port&gt; &lt;Service Account&gt; \nFor a named instance, use:\nsetspn -S MSSQLSvc/&lt;FQDN&gt;:&lt;instancename&gt; &lt;Service Account&gt; \nsetspn -S MSSQLSvc/&lt;FQDN&gt;:&lt;TCP Port&gt; &lt;Service Account&gt;\n\nRestart the SQL Server instance. \n\nMore information regarding this process is available at https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/database-engine/configure-windows/register-a-service-principal-name-for-kerberos-connections#Manual.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:301","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-271264, SV-271264r1111061, SRG-APP-000023-DB-000001)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000023-DB-000001","id":"V-271264"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:var:27126504;;Instance;;user_name;;Array","rule_id":"SV-271265r1108933","uuid":"43C7F7B8-6C08-1014-AF6F-D0E17703E3C2","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Enterprise environments make account management for applications and databases challenging and complex. A manual process for account management functions adds the risk of a potential oversight or other error. Managing accounts for the same person in multiple places is inefficient and prone to problems with consistency and synchronization. \n \nA comprehensive application account management process that includes automation helps to ensure that accounts designated as requiring attention are consistently and promptly addressed. \n \nExamples include, but are not limited to, using automation to act on multiple accounts designated as inactive, suspended, or terminated, or by disabling accounts located in noncentralized account stores, such as multiple servers. Account management functions can also include assignment of group or role membership; identifying account type; specifying user access authorizations (i.e., privileges); account removal, update, or termination; and administrative alerts. The use of automated mechanisms can include, for example, using email or text messaging to notify account managers when users are terminated or transferred; using the information system to monitor account usage; and using automated telephone notification to report atypical system account usage. \n \nSQL Server must be configured to automatically use organization-level account management functions, and these functions must immediately enforce the organization's current account policy. \n \nAutomation may be composed of differing technologies that when placed together contain an overall mechanism supporting an organization's automated account management requirements.","group_id_src":"V-271265","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271265r1108933_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000023-DB-000001","group_id":"V-271265","rule_title":"SQL Server must integrate with an organization-level authentication/access mechanism providing account management and automation for all users, groups, roles, and any other principals.","severity":"high","rule_version":"SQLI-22-003700","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000015"],"fix_text":"If mixed mode is required, document the need and justification; describe the measures taken to ensure the use of SQL Server authentication is kept to a minimum; describe the measures taken to safeguard passwords; and list or describe the SQL Logins used.\n\nDocumentation must be approved by the ISSO/ISSM.\n \nIf mixed mode is not required, disable it as follows:  \n \n1. In the SSMS Object Explorer, right-click on the server instance. \n2. Select Properties &gt;&gt; Security page.\n3. Click the radio button for \"Windows Authentication Mode\".\n4. Click \"OK\". \n5. Restart the SQL Server instance. \n \nOR  \n \nRun the statement:  \n\nUSE [master] \nEXEC xp_instance_regwrite N'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE', N'Software\\Microsoft\\MSSQLServer\\MSSQLServer', N'LoginMode', REG_DWORD, 2 \nGO \n \nRestart the SQL Server instance. \n \nFor each account being managed by SQL Server but not requiring it, drop or disable the SQL Login. Replace it with an appropriately configured account, as needed. \n \nTo drop or disable a login in the SSMS Object Explorer, navigate to \"Security Logins\". \nRight-click on the login name and click \"Delete\" or \"Disable\". \n \nTo drop or disable a login by using a query:  \n\nUSE master;  \nDROP LOGIN login_name; \nALTER LOGIN login_name DISABLE; \n \nDropping a login does not delete the equivalent database user(s). There may be more than one database containing a user mapped to the login. Drop the user(s) unless still needed. \n \nTo drop a user in the SSMS Object Explorer:  \nNavigate to Databases &gt;&gt; Security Users. \nRight-click on the username. \nClick \"Delete\". \n \nTo drop a user via a query:  \n\nUSE database_name; \nDROP USER &lt;user_name&gt;;","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271265","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (If Windows Authentication Mode is selected, this is not a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        authentication_mode = 'Windows and SQL Server Authentication' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'Windows Authentication' \nTest            :   false (If any accounts listed by the query are not listed in the documentation, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Collected Item did not meet the state requirement.\n","ia_controls":"","status":"open","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000023-DB-000001","id":"V-271265"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Review the system documentation to determine the required levels of protection for DBMS server securables by type of login. \n \nReview the permissions in place on the server. \n \nIf the permissions do not match the documented requirements, this is a finding. \n \nUse the supplemental file \"Instance permissions assignments to logins and roles.sql\".","rule_id":"SV-271266r1137654","uuid":"43C7FBC3-6C08-1014-8227-BC8702B63257","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Authentication with a DOD-approved PKI certificate does not necessarily imply authorization to access SQL Server. To mitigate the risk of unauthorized access to sensitive information by entities that have been issued certificates by DOD-approved PKIs, all DOD systems, including databases, must be properly configured to implement access control policies. \n \nSuccessful authentication must not automatically give an entity access to an asset or security boundary. Authorization procedures and controls must be implemented to ensure each authenticated entity also has a validated and current authorization. Authorization is the process of determining whether an entity, once authenticated, is permitted to access a specific asset. Information systems use access control policies and enforcement mechanisms to implement this requirement. \n \nAccess control policies include identity-based policies, role-based policies, and attribute-based policies. Access enforcement mechanisms include access control lists, access control matrices, and cryptography. These policies and mechanisms must be employed by the application to control access between users (or processes acting on behalf of users) and objects (e.g., devices, files, records, processes, programs, and domains) in the information system. \n \nThis requirement is applicable to access control enforcement applications, a category that includes database management systems. If SQL Server does not follow applicable policy when approving access, it may be in conflict with networks or other applications in the information system. This may result in users either gaining or being denied access inappropriately and in conflict with applicable policy.","group_id_src":"V-271266","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271266r1137654_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000033-DB-000084","group_id":"V-271266","rule_title":"SQL Server must enforce approved authorizations for logical access to information and system resources in accordance with applicable access control policies.","severity":"high","rule_version":"SQLI-22-003900","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"fix_text":"Use GRANT, REVOKE, DENY, ALTER SERVER ROLE â¦ ADD MEMBER â¦ and/or ALTER SERVER ROLE â¦. DROP MEMBER statements to add and remove permissions on server-level securables, bringing them into line with the documented requirements.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:701","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-271266, SV-271266r1137654, SRG-APP-000033-DB-000084)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000033-DB-000084","id":"V-271266"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Execute the following:\n\nSELECT name\nFROM sys.server_principals\nWHERE type in ('U','G')\nAND name LIKE '%$'\n\nIf no logins are returned, this is not a finding.\n\nIf logins are returned, determine whether each login is a computer account.\n\nLaunch PowerShell and execute the following code:\n\nNote: &lt;name&gt; represents the username portion of the login. For example, if the login is \"CONTOSO\\user1$\", the username is \"user1\".\n\n([ADSISearcher]\"(&amp;(ObjectCategory=Computer)(Name=&lt;name&gt;))\").FindAll()\n\nIf no account information is returned, this is not a finding.\n\nIf account information is returned, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271267r1108417","uuid":"43C7FFAF-6C08-1014-A1DB-DBFA03F60819","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Nonrepudiation of actions taken is required to maintain data integrity. Examples of particular actions taken by individuals include creating information, sending a message, approving information (e.g., indicating concurrence or signing a contract), and receiving a message. \n \nNonrepudiation protects against later claims by a user of not having created, modified, or deleted a particular data item or collection of data in the database. \n \nIn designing a database, the organization must define the types of data and the user actions that must be protected from repudiation. The implementation must then include building audit features into the application data tables and configuring the DBMS's audit tools to capture the necessary audit trail. Design and implementation also must ensure that applications pass individual user identification to the DBMS, even where the application connects to the DBMS with a standard, shared account. \n \nIf the computer account of a remote computer is granted access to SQL Server, any service or scheduled task running as NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM or NT AUTHORITY\\NETWORK SERVICE can log into the instance and perform actions. These actions cannot be traced back to a specific user or process.","group_id_src":"V-271267","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271267r1108417_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080-DB-000063","group_id":"V-271267","rule_title":"SQL Server must protect against a user falsely repudiating by ensuring only clearly unique Active Directory user accounts can connect to the instance.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-004200","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"fix_text":"Remove all logins that were returned in the check content.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271267","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Verify that none of the SQL logins are computer accounts.)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080-DB-000063","id":"V-271267"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Execute the following queries. The first query checks for clustering and availability groups being provisioned in the database engine. The second query lists permissions granted to the local system account.\n\nSELECT\n    SERVERPROPERTY('IsClustered') AS [IsClustered],\n    SERVERPROPERTY('IsHadrEnabled') AS [IsHadrEnabled]\n\nEXECUTE AS LOGIN = 'NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM'\n\nSELECT * FROM fn_my_permissions(NULL, 'server')\n\nREVERT\n\nGO\n\nIf \"IsClustered\" returns \"1\", \"IsHadrEnabled\" returns \"0\", and any permissions have been granted to the Local System account beyond \"CONNECT SQL\", \"VIEW SERVER STATE\", \"VIEW ANY DATABASE\", \"VIEW SERVER PERFORMANCE STATE\", and \"VIEW SERVER SECURITY STATE\", this is a finding.\n \nIf \"IsHadrEnabled\" returns \"1\" and any permissions have been granted to the Local System account beyond \"CONNECT SQL\", \"CREATE AVAILABILITY GROUP\", \"ALTER ANY AVAILABILITY GROUP\", \"VIEW SERVER STATE\", \"VIEW ANY DATABASE\", \"VIEW SERVER PERFORMANCE STATE\", and \"VIEW SERVER SECURITY STATE\", this is a finding.\n \nIf both \"IsClustered\" and \"IsHadrEnabled\" return \"0\" and any permissions have been granted to the Local System account beyond \"CONNECT SQL\" and \"VIEW ANY DATABASE\", this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271268r1136917","uuid":"43C803A0-6C08-1014-BADA-CBFA94AA9D85","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Nonrepudiation of actions taken is required to maintain data integrity. Examples of particular actions taken by individuals include creating information, sending a message, approving information (e.g., indicating concurrence or signing a contract), and receiving a message. \n \nNonrepudiation protects against later claims by a user of not having created, modified, or deleted a particular data item or collection of data in the database. \n \nIn designing a database, the organization must define the types of data and the user actions that must be protected from repudiation. The implementation must then include building audit features into the application data tables and configuring the DBMS's audit tools to capture the necessary audit trail. Design and implementation also must ensure that applications pass individual user identification to the DBMS, even where the application connects to the DBMS with a standard, shared account. \n \nAny user with enough access to the server can execute a task that will be run as NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM either using task scheduler or other tools. At this point, NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM essentially becomes a shared account because the operating system and SQL Server are unable to determine who created the process. \n \nPrior to SQL Server 2012, NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM was a member of the sysadmin role by default. This allowed jobs/tasks to be executed in SQL Server without the approval or knowledge of the DBA because it looked like operating system activity.","group_id_src":"V-271268","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271268r1136917_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080-DB-000063","group_id":"V-271268","rule_title":"SQL Server must protect against a user falsely repudiating by ensuring the NT AUTHORITY SYSTEM account is not used for administration.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-004100","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"fix_text":"Remove permissions that were identified as not allowed in the check content.\n\nUSE Master;\n\nREVOKE &lt;Permission&gt; TO [NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM]\n\nGO\n\nTo grant permissions to services or applications, use the Service SID of the service or a domain service account.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271268","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: errorRule Result     : Error\nCriteria        : error (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     false (IsClustered returns 1)\nResult Analysis :          Collected Item did not meet the state requirement.\nTest            :     true (IsHadrEnabled returns 0)\nTest            :     error (Permissions granted to the Local System account CONNECT SQL, VIEW SERVER STATE, VIEW ANY DATABASE, VIEW SERVER PERFORMANCE STATE, and VIEW SERVER SECURITY STATE)\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     false (IsHadrEnabled returns 1)\nResult Analysis :          Collected Item did not meet the state requirement.\nTest            :     error (Permissions granted to the Local System account beyond CONNECT SQL, CREATE AVAILABILITY GROUP, ALTER ANY AVAILABILITY GROUP, VIEW SERVER STATE, VIEW ANY DATABASE, VIEW SERVER PERFORMANCE STATE, and VIEW SERVER SECURITY STATE)\nCriteria        :   error (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (IsClustered returns 0)\nTest            :     true (IsHadrEnabled returns 0)\nTest            :     error (Permissions granted to the Local System account beyond CONNECT SQL and VIEW ANY DATABASE)\nError Informatio: Unable to retrieve any data with SQL transaction \"EXECUTE AS LOGIN = 'NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM';\n                : SELECT * FROM fn_my_permissions(NULL, 'server')\n                : WHERE permission_name NOT IN ('CONNECT SQL', 'VIEW ANY DATABASE');\n                : REVERT;\n                :  from DBMS instance \"SQLEXPRESS\" on server \"SOT-WIN2K22-SQL\" Error: [Microsoft][ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server][SQL Server]Cannot execute as the server principal because the principal \"NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM\" does not exist, this type of principal cannot be impersonated, or you do not have permission. (SQL-42000)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"open","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080-DB-000063","id":"V-271268"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:var:27126904;;Instance;;user_name;;Array","rule_id":"SV-271269r1108423","uuid":"43C80787-6C08-1014-8879-B6E47B2DF801","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Nonrepudiation of actions taken is required to maintain data integrity. Examples of particular actions taken by individuals include creating information, sending a message, approving information (e.g., indicating concurrence or signing a contract), and receiving a message. \n \nNonrepudiation protects against later claims by a user of not having created, modified, or deleted a particular data item or collection of data in the database. \n \nIn designing a database, the organization must define the types of data and the user actions that must be protected from repudiation. The implementation must then include building audit features into the application data tables and configuring SQL Server's audit tools to capture the necessary audit trail. Design and implementation also must ensure that applications pass individual user identification to SQL Server, even where the application connects to SQL Server with a standard, shared account.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000080-DB-000063, SRG-APP-000815-DB-000160","group_id_src":"V-271269","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271269r1108423_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080-DB-000063","group_id":"V-271269","rule_title":"SQL Server must protect against a user falsely repudiating by ensuring all accounts are individual, unique, and not shared.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-004000","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000166","CCI-004045"],"fix_text":"Remove user-accessible shared accounts and use individual user IDs. \n \nBuild/configure applications to ensure successful individual authentication prior to shared account access. \n \nEnsure each user's identity is received and used in audit data in all relevant circumstances. \n \nDesign, develop, and implement a method to log use of any account to which more than one person has access. Restrict interactive access to shared accounts to the fewest persons possible.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271269","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (If shared identifiers are found, and not accompanied by individual identifiers, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Collected Item did not meet the state requirement.\nTest            :   true (If logins are links to computer accounts this is a finding.)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"open","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080-DB-000063","id":"V-271269"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:var:27127004;;Instance;;action_name;;Array","rule_id":"SV-271270r1108426","uuid":"43C80B69-6C08-1014-92F4-DD414E01C998","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Without the capability to generate audit records, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one. \n \nAudit records can be generated from various components within SQL Server (e.g., process, module). Certain specific application functionalities may be audited as well. The list of audited events is the set of events for which audits are to be generated. This set of events is typically a subset of the list of all events for which the system is capable of generating audit records. \n \nDOD has defined the list of events for which SQL Server will provide an audit record generation capability as the following:  \n \n(i) Successful and unsuccessful attempts to access, modify, or delete privileges, security objects, security levels, or categories of information (e.g., classification levels); \n \n(ii) Access actions, such as successful and unsuccessful logon attempts, privileged activities, or other system-level access, starting and ending time for user access to the system, concurrent logons from different workstations, successful and unsuccessful accesses to objects, all program initiations, and all direct access to the information system; and \n \n(iii) All account creation, modification, disabling, and termination actions. \n \nOrganizations may define additional events requiring continuous or ad hoc auditing.","group_id_src":"V-271270","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271270r1108426_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089-DB-000064","group_id":"V-271270","rule_title":"SQL Server must be configured to generate audit records for DOD-defined auditable events within all DBMS/database components.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-004300","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"fix_text":"Add all required audit events to the STIG-compliant audit specification server documentation.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271270","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   error (All currently defined audits for the SQL server instance will be listed. If no audits are returned, this is a finding.)\nTest            :   false (Compare the documentation to the list of generated audit events. If there are any missing events, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        '' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to '' \n","ia_controls":"","status":"open","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089-DB-000064","id":"V-271270"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Obtain the list of approved audit maintainers from the system documentation. \n \nReview the server roles and individual logins that have the following role memberships, all of which enable the ability to create and maintain audit definitions. \n \nsysadmin \ndbcreator \n \nReview the server roles and individual logins that have the following permissions, all of which enable the ability to create and maintain audit definitions. \n \nALTER ANY SERVER AUDIT  \nCONTROL SERVER  \nALTER ANY DATABASE  \nCREATE ANY DATABASE \n \nUse the following query to determine the roles and logins that have the listed permissions: \n \nSELECT-- DISTINCT \n    CASE \n        WHEN SP.class_desc IS NOT NULL THEN  \n            CASE \n                WHEN SP.class_desc = 'SERVER' AND S.is_linked = 0 THEN 'SERVER' \n                WHEN SP.class_desc = 'SERVER' AND S.is_linked = 1 THEN 'SERVER (linked)' \n                ELSE SP.class_desc \n            END \n        WHEN E.name IS NOT NULL THEN 'ENDPOINT' \n        WHEN S.name IS NOT NULL AND S.is_linked = 0 THEN 'SERVER' \n        WHEN S.name IS NOT NULL AND S.is_linked = 1 THEN 'SERVER (linked)' \n        WHEN P.name IS NOT NULL THEN 'SERVER_PRINCIPAL' \n        ELSE '???'  \n    END                    AS [Securable Class], \n    CASE \n        WHEN E.name IS NOT NULL THEN E.name \n        WHEN S.name IS NOT NULL THEN S.name  \n        WHEN P.name IS NOT NULL THEN P.name \n        ELSE '???'  \n    END                    AS [Securable], \n    P1.name                AS [Grantee], \n    P1.type_desc           AS [Grantee Type], \n    sp.permission_name     AS [Permission], \n    sp.state_desc          AS [State], \n    P2.name                AS [Grantor], \n    P2.type_desc           AS [Grantor Type], \nR.name    AS [Role Name] \nFROM \n    sys.server_permissions SP \n    INNER JOIN sys.server_principals P1 \n        ON P1.principal_id = SP.grantee_principal_id \n    INNER JOIN sys.server_principals P2 \n        ON P2.principal_id = SP.grantor_principal_id \n \n    FULL OUTER JOIN sys.servers S \n        ON  SP.class_desc = 'SERVER' \n        AND S.server_id = SP.major_id \n \n    FULL OUTER JOIN sys.endpoints E \n        ON  SP.class_desc = 'ENDPOINT' \n        AND E.endpoint_id = SP.major_id \n \n    FULL OUTER JOIN sys.server_principals P \n        ON  SP.class_desc = 'SERVER_PRINCIPAL'         \n        AND P.principal_id = SP.major_id \n \nFULL OUTER JOIN sys.server_role_members SRM \nON P.principal_id = SRM.member_principal_id \n \nLEFT OUTER JOIN sys.server_principals R \nON SRM.role_principal_id = R.principal_id \nWHERE sp.permission_name IN ('ALTER ANY SERVER AUDIT','CONTROL SERVER','ALTER ANY DATABASE','CREATE ANY DATABASE') \nOR R.name IN ('sysadmin','dbcreator') \n \nIf any of the logins, roles, or role memberships returned have permissions that are not documented, or the documented audit maintainers do not have permissions, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271271r1108429","uuid":"43C81705-6C08-1014-A1ED-D280AFF31608","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Without the capability to restrict which roles and individuals can select which events are audited, unauthorized personnel may be able to prevent or interfere with the auditing of critical events. \n \nSuppression of auditing could permit an adversary to evade detection. \n \nMisconfigured audits can degrade the system's performance by overwhelming the audit log. Misconfigured audits may also make it more difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.","group_id_src":"V-271271","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271271r1108429_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000090-DB-000065","group_id":"V-271271","rule_title":"SQL Server must allow only the information system security manager (ISSM) (or individuals or roles appointed by the ISSM) to select which auditable events are to be audited.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-004400","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000171"],"fix_text":"Create a server role specifically for audit maintainers and give it permission to maintain audits without granting it unnecessary permissions (the role name used here is an example; other names may be used):\n \nCREATE SERVER ROLE SERVER_AUDIT_MAINTAINERS; \nGO \n \nGRANT ALTER ANY SERVER AUDIT TO SERVER_AUDIT_MAINTAINERS; \nGO     \n \nUse REVOKE and/or DENY and/or ALTER SERVER ROLE ... DROP MEMBER ... statements to remove the ALTER ANY SERVER AUDIT permission from all logins. Then, for each authorized login, run the statement:\n \nALTER SERVER ROLE SERVER_AUDIT_MAINTAINERS ADD MEMBER; \nGO \n \nUse REVOKE and/or DENY and/or ALTER SERVER ROLE ... DROP MEMBER ... statements to remove CONTROL SERVER, ALTER ANY DATABASE and CREATE ANY DATABASE permissions from logins that do not need them.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:1701","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-271271, SV-271271r1108429, SRG-APP-000090-DB-000065)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000090-DB-000065","id":"V-271271"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Review the system documentation to determine if SQL Server is required to audit when the following events occur:\n\n- Attempts to retrieve privilege/permission/role membership information.\n- Security objects are accessed, modified, or deleted.\n- Data classifications (e.g., classification levels/security levels) are accessed, modified, or deleted.\n- Any other specified objects are accessed, modified, or deleted as required by the site.\n\nIf SQL Server is not required to audit any of the above, this is not a finding. \n \nIf the documentation does not exist, this is a finding. \n \nDetermine if an audit is configured and started by executing the following query. If no records are returned, this is a finding. \n \nSELECT name AS 'Audit Name', \nstatus_desc AS 'Audit Status', \naudit_file_path AS 'Current Audit File' \nFROM sys.dm_server_audit_status \n \nIf auditing the retrieval of the above information or objects is required, execute the following to verify the SCHEMA_OBJECT_ACCESS_GROUP is included in the server audit specification: \n \nSELECT a.name AS 'AuditName', \ns.name AS 'SpecName', \nd.audit_action_name AS 'ActionName', \nd.audited_result AS 'Result' \nFROM sys.server_audit_specifications s \nJOIN sys.server_audits a ON s.audit_guid = a.audit_guid \nJOIN sys.server_audit_specification_details d ON s.server_specification_id = d.server_specification_id \nWHERE a.is_state_enabled = 1 AND d.audit_action_name = 'SCHEMA_OBJECT_ACCESS_GROUP' \n \nIf the SCHEMA_OBJECT_ACCESS_GROUP is not returned in an active audit, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271272r1109110","uuid":"43C81BC3-6C08-1014-9073-EC3DC1F6C68E","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Under some circumstances, it may be useful to monitor who/what is reading privilege/permission/role information. Therefore, monitoring must be possible. DBMSs typically make such information available through views or functions.\n \nThis requirement includes explicit requests for privilege/permission/role membership information. It does not refer to the implicit retrieval of privileges/permissions/role memberships that SQL Server continually performs to determine if any and every action on the database is permitted. \n\nChanges to the security configuration must also be tracked. \n\nSecurity configuration tracking applies to situations where security data is retrieved or modified via data manipulation operations, as opposed to via specialized security functionality. \n\nIn a SQL environment, types of access include but are not necessarily limited to: \nSELECT \nINSERT \nUPDATE \nDELETE \nEXECUTE\n\nChanges in categorized information must be tracked. Without an audit trail, unauthorized access to protected data could go undetected. \n \nFor detailed information on categorizing information, refer to FIPS Publication 199, Standards for Security Categorization of Federal Information and Information Systems, and FIPS Publication 200, Minimum Security Requirements for Federal Information and Information Systems.\n \nTo aid in diagnosis, it is necessary to track failed attempts in addition to the successful ones.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000091-DB-000325, SRG-APP-000091-DB-000066, SRG-APP-000492-DB-000332, SRG-APP-000492-DB-000333, SRG-APP-000494-DB-000344, SRG-APP-000494-DB-000345, SRG-APP-000498-DB-000346, SRG-APP-000498-DB-000347, SRG-APP-000502-DB-000348, SRG-APP-000502-DB-000349, SRG-APP-000507-DB-000356, SRG-APP-000507-DB-000357","group_id_src":"V-271272","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271272r1109110_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000091-DB-000325","group_id":"V-271272","rule_title":"SQL Server must generate audit records when attempts to access privileges, categorized information, and security objects occur.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-004600","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"fix_text":"Deploy an audit to log when attempts to access privileges, categorized information, security objects, and any other specific objects occur. \n\nRefer to the supplemental file \"SQL 2022 Audit.sql\".","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271272","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   error (All currently defined audits for the SQL server instance will be listed. If no audits are returned, this is a finding.)\nTest            :   false (If the SCHEMA_OBJECT_ACCESS_GROUP is not returned in an active audit, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        .  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :         .  \n","ia_controls":"","status":"open","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000091-DB-000325","id":"V-271272"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"When audits are enabled, they start up when the instance starts. Refer to https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc280386.aspx#Anchor_2 \n \nCheck if an audit is configured and enabled by executing the following query: \n \nSELECT name AS 'Audit Name', \nstatus_desc AS 'Audit Status', \naudit_file_path AS 'Current Audit File' \nFROM sys.dm_server_audit_status \nWHERE status_desc = 'STARTED' \n \nAll currently defined audits for the SQL server instance will be listed. If no audits are returned, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271273r1109234","uuid":"43C8209C-6C08-1014-BE7A-8D29141908BB","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Session auditing is for use when a user's activities are under investigation. To be sure of capturing all activity during those periods when session auditing is in use, it needs to be in operation for the whole time SQL Server is running.","group_id_src":"V-271273","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271273r1109234_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000092-DB-000208","group_id":"V-271273","rule_title":"SQL Server must initiate session auditing upon startup.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-004700","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001464"],"fix_text":"Configure the SQL audit(s) to automatically start during system startup. \n \nALTER SERVER AUDIT [&lt;Server Audit Name&gt;] WITH STATE = ON \n \nExecute the following: \n \nSELECT name AS 'Audit Name', \n  status_desc AS 'Audit Status', \n  audit_file_path AS 'Current Audit File' \nFROM sys.dm_server_audit_status \nWHERE status_desc = 'STARTED' \n \nEnsure the SQL STIG Audit is configured to initiate session auditing upon startup.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271273","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: errorRule Result     : Error\nCriteria        : error (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   error (All currently defined audits for the SQL server instance will be listed. If no audits are returned, this is a finding.)\nError Informatio: Unable to retrieve any data with SQL transaction \"SELECT name AS 'Audit Name', \n                : status_desc AS 'Audit Status', \n                : audit_file_path AS 'Current Audit File' \n                : FROM sys.dm_server_audit_status \n                : WHERE status_desc = 'STARTED' from DBMS instance \"SQLEXPRESS\" on server \"SOT-WIN2K22-SQL\" Error: [Microsoft][ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server][SQL Server]VIEW SERVER SECURITY STATE permission was denied on object 'server', database 'master'. (SQL-42000)\n                : [Microsoft][ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server][SQL Server]The user does not have permission to perform this action. (SQL-42000)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"open","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000092-DB-000208","id":"V-271273"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"If a SQL Server Audit is not in use for audit purposes, this is a finding unless a third-party product is being used that can perform detailed auditing for SQL Server. \n \nReview system documentation to determine whether SQL Server is required to audit any events, and any fields, in addition to those in the standard audit. \n \nIf there are none specified, this is not a finding. \n \nIf SQL Server Audit is in use, compare the audit specification(s) with the documented requirements. \n \nIf any such requirement is not satisfied by the audit specification(s) (or by supplemental, locally deployed mechanisms), this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271280r1108456","uuid":"43C82483-6C08-1014-A3CA-AB8DFACE05AE","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Information system auditing capability is critical for accurate forensic analysis. Reconstruction of harmful events or forensic analysis is not possible if audit records do not contain enough information. To support analysis, some types of events will need information to be logged that exceeds the basic requirements of event type, time stamps, location, source, outcome, and user identity. If additional information is not available, it could negatively impact forensic investigations into user actions or other malicious events. \n \nThe organization must determine what additional information is required for complete analysis of the audited events. The additional information required is dependent on the type of information (e.g., sensitivity of the data and the environment within which it resides). At a minimum, the organization must employ either full-text recording of privileged commands or the individual identities of users of shared accounts, or both. The organization must maintain audit trails in sufficient detail to reconstruct events to determine the cause and impact of compromise. \n \nExamples of detailed information the organization may require in audit records are full-text recording of privileged commands or the individual identities of shared account users.","group_id_src":"V-271280","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271280r1108456_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000101-DB-000044","group_id":"V-271280","rule_title":"SQL Server must include additional, more detailed, organization-defined information in the audit records for audit events identified by type, location, or subject.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-005500","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000135"],"fix_text":"Design and deploy an audit that captures all auditable events and data items. In the event a third-party tool is used for auditing, it must contain all the required information, including but not limited to, events, type, location, subject, date and time, and by whom the change occurred. \n \nImplement additional custom audits to capture the additional organizational required information.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:2301","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-271280, SV-271280r1108456, SRG-APP-000101-DB-000044)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000101-DB-000044","id":"V-271280"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"If the database is set up to write audit logs using APPLICATION or SECURITY event logs rather than writing to a file, this is Not Applicable.\n\nObtain the SQL Server Audit file location(s) by running the following SQL script:  \n\nSELECT log_file_path AS \"Audit Path\"  \nFROM sys.server_file_audits  \n\nFor each audit, the path column will give the location of the file. \n\nVerify that all audit files have the correct permissions by doing the following for each audit file: Navigate to audit folder location(s) using a command prompt or Windows Explorer. \n\nRight-click the file/folder and click \"Properties\". On the \"Security\" tab, verify the following permissions are applied:  \n\nAdministrator (read)  \nUsers (none)  \nAudit Administrator (Full Control)  \nAuditors group (Read)  \nSQL Server Service SID OR Service Account (Full Control)  \nSQL Server SQL Agent Service SID OR Service Account, if SQL Server Agent is in use. (Read, Execute, Write) \n\nIf any less restrictive permissions are present (and not specifically justified and approved), this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-271282r1109273","uuid":"43C82919-6C08-1014-9120-EF1A7C64FC66","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"If audit data were to become compromised,  competent forensic analysis and discovery of the true source of potentially malicious system activity would be difficult, if not impossible, to achieve. In addition, access to audit records provides information an attacker could potentially use to their advantage. \n\nTo ensure the veracity of audit data, the information system and/or the application must protect audit information from any and all unauthorized access. This includes read, write, copy, etc. \n\nThis requirement can be achieved through multiple methods, which will depend on system architecture and design. Some commonly employed methods include ensuring log files enjoy the proper file system permissions using file system protections and limiting log data location. \n\nAdditionally, applications with user interfaces to audit records should not allow for the unfettered manipulation of or access to those records via the application. If the application provides access to the audit data, the application becomes accountable for ensuring that audit information is protected from unauthorized access. SQL Server is able to view and manipulate audit file data. \n\nAudit information includes all information (e.g., audit records, audit settings, and audit reports) needed to successfully audit information system activity.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000118-DB-000059, SRG-APP-000119-DB-000060, SRG-APP-000120-DB-000061","group_id_src":"V-271282","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271282r1109273_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000118-DB-000059","group_id":"V-271282","rule_title":"The audit information produced by SQL Server must be protected from unauthorized access, modification, and deletion.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-005900","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"fix_text":"Modify audit file permissions to meet the requirement to protect against unauthorized access. \n\nApplication event log and security log permissions are covered in the Windows Server STIGs. Reference these depending on the OS in use.\n\nNavigate to audit folder location(s) using a command prompt or Windows Explorer. Right-click the file and click \"Properties\". \n\nOn the Security tab, modify the security permissions to:  \n\nAdministrator (read)  \nUsers (none)  \nAudit Administrator(Full Control)  \nAuditors group (Read)  \nSQL Server Service SID OR Service Account (Full Control) [Notes 1, 2]  \nSQL Server SQL Agent Service SID OR Service Account, if SQL Server Agent is in use. (Read, Execute, Write) [Notes 1, 2]  \n\n-----  \nNote 1: It is highly advisable to use a separate account for each service. When installing SQL Server in single-server mode, users can opt to have these provisioned for them. These automatically generated accounts are referred to as virtual accounts. Each virtual account has an equivalent Service SID with the same name. The installer also creates an equivalent SQL Server login, also with the same name. Applying folder and file permissions to Service SIDs rather than to domain accounts or local computer accounts provides tighter control, because these permissions are available only to the specific service when it is running and not in any other context. However, when using failover clustering, a domain account must be specified at installation, rather than a virtual account. For more on this topic, refer to http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms143504(v=sql.130).aspx. \n\nNote 2: Tips for adding a service SID/virtual account to a folder's permission list:\n\n1. In Windows Explorer, right-click the folder and select \"Properties\". \n2. Select the \"Security\" tab. \n3. Click \"Edit\". \n4. Click \"Add\". \n5. Click \"Locations\". \n6. Select the computer name. \n7. Search for the name. \n   7.a. SQL Server Service  \n   7.a.i. Type \"NT SERVICE\\MSSQL\" and click \"Check Names\". (This is the first 16 characters of the name. At least one character must follow \"NT SERVICE\\\"; this will present with a list of all matches. If the full, correct name was typed, step 7.a.ii is bypassed.)  \n   7.a.ii. Select the \"MSSQL$\" user and click \"OK\".\n   7.b. SQL Agent Service  \n   7.b.i. Type \"NT SERVICE\\SQL\" and click \"Check Names\". \n   7.b.ii. Select the \"SQLAgent$\" user and click \"OK\". \n8. Click \"OK\". \n9. Permission like a normal user from here.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:2501","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-271282, SV-271282r1109273, SRG-APP-000118-DB-000059)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000118-DB-000059","id":"V-271282"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:var:27128304;;Instance;;user_name;;Array","rule_id":"SV-271283r1108465","uuid":"43C82D49-6C08-1014-AF03-B1F18C5764AD","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"Protecting audit data also includes identifying and protecting the tools used to view and manipulate log data. Therefore, protecting audit tools is necessary to prevent unauthorized operation on audit data. \n \nApplications providing tools to interface with audit data will leverage user permissions and roles identifying the user accessing the tools and the corresponding rights the user enjoys in order make access decisions regarding the modification of audit tools. SQL Server is an application that does provide access to audit data. \n \nAudit tools include, but are not limited to, vendor-provided and open-source audit tools needed to successfully view and manipulate audit information system activity and records. Audit tools include custom queries and report generators.\n\nIf an attacker were to gain access to audit tools, they could analyze audit logs for system weaknesses or weaknesses in the auditing itself. An attacker could also manipulate logs to hide evidence of malicious activity.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000121-DB-000202, SRG-APP-000122-DB-000203, SRG-APP-000123-DB-000204","group_id_src":"V-271283","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271283r1108465_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000121-DB-000202","group_id":"V-271283","rule_title":"SQL Server must protect its audit configuration from authorized and unauthorized access and modification.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-006300","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001493","CCI-001494","CCI-001495"],"fix_text":"Remove audit-related permissions from individuals and roles not authorized to have them. \n \nUSE master;   \nDENY [ALTER ANY SERVER AUDIT] TO [User];   \nGO","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271283","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (If unauthorized accounts have these privileges, this is a finding.)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_a_finding","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000121-DB-000202","id":"V-271283"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Review server documentation to determine the process by which shared software libraries are monitored for change. Ensure the process alerts for changes in a file's ownership, modification dates, and hash value at a minimum.\n\nIf alerts do not at least hash their value, this is a finding.\n\nTo determine the location for these instance-specific binaries:\n\n1. Launch SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS).\n2. Connect to the instance to be reviewed.\n3. Right-click server name in Object Explorer.\n4. Click \"Facets\".\n5. Select the \"Server\" facet.\n6. Record the value for the \"RootDirectory\" facet property.\n\nTip: Use the Get-FileHash cmdlet shipped with PowerShell 5.0 to get the SHA-2 hash of one or more files.","rule_id":"SV-271284r1109111","uuid":"43C830F2-6C08-1014-AA9A-CFDD9B57F01A","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"If the system were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process. \n \nAccordingly, only qualified and authorized individuals must be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications. \n \nUnmanaged changes that occur to the database software libraries or configuration can lead to unauthorized or compromised installations.","group_id_src":"V-271284","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271284r1109111_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000133-DB-000179","group_id":"V-271284","rule_title":"SQL Server must limit privileges to change software modules, to include stored procedures, functions and triggers, and links to software external to SQL Server.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-006600","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"fix_text":"Implement and document a process by which changes made to software libraries are monitored and alerted. A PowerShell based hashing solution is one such process. The Get-FileHash command can be used to compute the SHA-2 hash of one or more files. For more information, refer to the following link:\nhttps://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/reference/5.1/microsoft.powershell.utility/get-filehash\n\nUsing the Export-Clixml command, a baseline can be established and exported to a file:\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/microsoft.powershell.utility/export-clixml?view=powershell-7.5\n\nUsing the Compare-Object command, a comparison of the latest baseline versus the original baseline can expose the differences:\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/windows/it-pro/windows-powershell-1.0/ee156812(v=technet.10)?redirectedfrom=MSDN","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:2901","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-271284, SV-271284r1109111, SRG-APP-000133-DB-000179)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000133-DB-000179","id":"V-271284"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"Review Server documentation to determine the authorized owner and users or groups with modify rights for this SQL instance's binary files. Additionally check the owner and users or groups with modify rights for shared software library paths on disk. \n \nIf any unauthorized users are granted modify rights or the owner is incorrect, this is a finding. \n\nTo determine the location for these instance-specific binaries:\n\n1. Launch SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS). \n2. Connect to the instance to be reviewed. \n3. Right-click server name in \"Object Explorer\".\n4. Click \"Facets\".\n5. Select the \"Server\" facet. \n6. Record the value for the \"RootDirectory\" facet property. \n7. Navigate to the folder above and review the \"Binn\" subdirectory.\n\nTIP: Use the Get-FileHash cmdlet shipped with PowerShell 5.0 to get the SHA-2 hash of one or more files.","rule_id":"SV-271285r1109236","uuid":"43C83477-6C08-1014-A342-AEDC511CB379","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"If the system were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process. \n \nAccordingly, only qualified and authorized individuals must be allowed to obtain access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications. \n \nUnmanaged changes that occur to the database software libraries or configuration can lead to unauthorized or compromised installations.","group_id_src":"V-271285","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271285r1109236_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000133-DB-000179","group_id":"V-271285","rule_title":"SQL Server must limit privileges to change software modules and links to software external to SQL Server.","severity":"medium","rule_version":"SQLI-22-006500","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"fix_text":"Change the ownership of all shared software libraries on disk to the authorized account. Remove any modify permissions granted to unauthorized users or groups.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.sql.server:questionnaire:3101","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-ocil.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-271285, SV-271285r1109236, SRG-APP-000133-DB-000179)\n","ia_controls":"","status":"not_reviewed","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000133-DB-000179","id":"V-271285"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigations":"","reference_identifier":"5677","responsibility":"","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"43C3A5E2-6C08-1014-9A64-8906C4E0D1ED","comments":null},{"false_positives":"","check_content":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:var:27128602;;Instance;;user_name;;Array","rule_id":"SV-271286r1108474","uuid":"43C83804-6C08-1014-B573-BF78FA0D978F","mitigation_control":"","discussion":"When dealing with change control issues, it should be noted any changes to the hardware, software, and/or firmware components of the information system and/or application can have significant effects on the overall security of the system. \n\nIf the system were to allow any user to make changes to software libraries, then those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process. Accordingly, only qualified and authorized individuals must be allowed access to information system components for purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications. \n\nDBA and other privileged administrative or application owner accounts are granted privileges that allow actions that can have a great impact on SQL Server security and operation. It is especially important to grant privileged access to only those persons who are qualified and authorized to use them.","group_id_src":"V-271286","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","rule_id_src":"SV-271286r1108474_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000133-DB-000198","group_id":"V-271286","rule_title":"SQL Server software installation account must be restricted to authorized users.","severity":"high","rule_version":"SQLI-22-006700","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"fix_text":"From a command prompt, open lusrmgr.msc. Navigate to \"Users\" and right-click \"Individual User\". Select \"Properties\", then \"Member Of\". \n \nConfigure SQL Server and OS settings and access controls to restrict user access to objects and data that the user is authorized to view/use.","potential_impacts":"","weight":"10.0","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.sql.server.inst:def:271286","href":"U_MS_SQL_Server_2022_Instance_V1R3_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV6-oval2.xml"},"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:56:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Check all SQL 2016 bootstrap logs for LogonUser =.)\nResult Analysis :          Either filepath does not exist, or required pattern not found in: '\\.*\\.log$ ' pattern: 'LogonUser = (\\w+)'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     false (Verify SQL Instance is SQL 2016)\nResult Analysis :          '2022' failed test of 'equals' compared to '2016' \nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Check all SQL 2017 bootstrap logs for LogonUser =.)\nResult Analysis :          Either filepath does not exist, or required pattern not found in: '\\.*\\.log$ ' pattern: 'LogonUser = (\\w+)'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     false (Verify SQL Instance is SQL 2017)\nResult Analysis :          '2022' failed test of 'equals' compared to '2017' \nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Check all SQL 2019 bootstrap logs for LogonUser =.)\nResult Analysis :          Either filepath does not exist, or required pattern not found in: '\\.*\\.log$ ' pattern: 'LogonUser = (\\w+)'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     false (Verify SQL Instance is SQL 2019)\nResult Analysis :          '2022' failed test of 'equals' compared to '2019' \nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Check all SQL 2022 bootstrap logs for LogonUser =.)\nResult Analysis :          For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\AdvancedAnalytics_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\RsFx_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\SqlBrowser_Cpu32_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\SqlSupport_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\SqlWriter_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\conn_info_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\conn_info_loc_Cpu64_1033_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\msodbcsql_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\msoledbsql_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\smo_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\smo_extensions_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\smo_extensions_loc_Cpu64_1033_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\smo_loc_Cpu64_1033_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\sql_batchparser_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\sql_common_core_Cpu64_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110130\\sql_common_core_loc_Cpu64_1033_1.log': 'soteria' failed test of 'case insensitive equals' compared to ''\n                : For 'C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\160\\Setup Bootstrap\\Log\\20240202_110